+/**
+ * `reckoner.tick` — periodic-tick relay.
+ *
+ * Wired into the apparatus's `supportKit.relays` and paired with a
+ * standing order at `@every 60s` under `supportKit.standingOrders`,
+ * the relay sweeps every currently-held petition (writs in `new`
+ * carrying `ext.reckoner`) on each fire, runs source/disabled +
+ * dependency gates inline, and hands the surviving candidate set to
+ * the registry-resolved active scheduler in one batched
+ * `evaluate()` call. Each consideration produces at most one
+ * Reckonings row.
+ *
+ * The relay replaces the older CDC observer the Reckoner used to
+ * register on `clerk/writs`. The CDC path could only feed the
+ * scheduler one writ at a time and so could not support a
+ * priority-walk or any capacity-aware policy that needs the global
+ * candidate-set view; the tick path unifies pre-existing held writs
+ * and newly-arrived ones through one evaluation surface.
+ *
+ * The handler body is broken out as a pure helper (`runTickHandler`)
+ * so unit tests can drive it directly with a synthetic event id (or
+ * `null`) without booting Clockworks. The relay factory
+ * (`createTickRelay`) takes the same dependency context object the
+ * helper does — both consume the `TickHandlerContext` interface
+ * `buildReckoner()` constructs — so the closure-scoped state
+ * (registry maps, the resolved active scheduler, alreadyConsidered,
+ * the Reckonings book handle, config / scheduler-config resolvers,
+ * resolveActiveTargetPhase, buildReckoningRow) reaches the handler
+ * without going through `guild()` lookups inside the relay.
+ *
+ * Per-fire sequence (D8/D10/D7/D6/D9 from the originating brief):
+ *
+ *   1. Pre-seal guard — throw fail-loud when the active scheduler
+ *      reference has not been resolved yet (D8). Production never
+ *      trips this; test fixtures get a deterministic loud signal
+ *      when they drive the tick before firing `phase:started`.
+ *   2. Re-read + validate `reckoner.schedulerConfig` once per fire
+ *      via the active scheduler's `validateConfig`. A throw is
+ *      logged fail-loud and skips the entire tick (no rows, no
+ *      transitions).
+ *   3. Query held writs via `stacks.readBook<WritDoc>('clerk',
+ *      'writs')` filtered to `phase = 'new'` + `ext.reckoner`.
+ *   4. Empty-candidate early-return (D10): write nothing, no rows,
+ *      no errors. The scheduler is not called.
+ *   5. Source/disabled gates inline. A disabled-source writ produces
+ *      a `declined` row (`declineReason: 'source_banned'`,
+ *      `remediationHint` = the source name) and transitions to
+ *      `cancelled` (D2). An unregistered source under
+ *      `enforceRegistration: true` produces a `declined` row
+ *      (`declineReason: 'source_unregistered'`) and transitions to
+ *      `cancelled`, preserving the existing resolution-string
+ *      format.
+ *   6. Dependency gate per writ (preserved from the per-call CDC
+ *      path). Defer outcomes write `deferred` rows with
+ *      `deferReason: 'dependency_pending' | 'dependency_failed'`
+ *      and `deferNote` listing the gating / failed dep ids,
+ *      suppressing the row write when the outcome shape matches the
+ *      writ's most recent deferred row (no-op-row suppression).
+ *   7. Dedupe filter (D7) — drop writs whose
+ *      `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` pair already has a non-deferred
+ *      Reckonings row. Already-considered writs never reach the
+ *      scheduler.
+ *   8. Build one `SchedulerInput { candidates, capacity, now,
+ *      config }` for the entire surviving candidate set with the v0
+ *      capacity stub.
+ *   9. `evaluate` inside a try/catch. A throw is logged fail-loud
+ *      and skips the whole tick (no rows for any writ). A
+ *      non-array return is treated identically.
+ *  10. Decision validation. Stranger writIds are filter-and-warned
+ *      (apply only in-scope decisions). Multi-decision-per-writ
+ *      fail-loud-skips the entire tick (no rows for any writ in
+ *      this tick).
+ *  11. Apply each decision. `approve` → transition to active target
+ *      via `resolveActiveTargetPhase` + `accepted` row. `decline` →
+ *      transition to `cancelled` with the decision's reason as
+ *      resolution + `declined` row carrying `declineReason: 'other'`
+ *      and the reason in `remediationHint`. `defer` → no transition;
+ *      write a `deferred` row with `deferReason: 'other'` and the
+ *      decision's reason in `deferNote` (D3).
+ *  12. Stamp `tickEventId` on every row from the triggering
+ *      `clockworks.timer` event id when `event` is non-null (D6);
+ *      omit the field when the helper was driven directly with
+ *      `null` (test paths).
+ *
+ * See: docs/architecture/apparatus/reckoner.md (the apparatus
+ * shape) and docs/architecture/reckonings-book.md (the schema for
+ * the journal rows this handler writes).
+ */
+
+import type { GuildEvent, RelayDefinition } from '@shardworks/clockworks-apparatus';
+import { relay } from '@shardworks/clockworks-apparatus';
+
+import type { Book, ReadOnlyBook, StacksApi } from '@shardworks/stacks-apparatus';
+import type {
+  ClerkApi,
